Date:  0/0/1839
Source:  Important Information Relative to NZ
Author:
Vol / Page:  29
Edition:
Quote:   ... two grog-shops <i>IBid.</i> 1840 108 There are upwards of 2000 British subjects now settled in different parts of the islands, of whom several hundreds consist of a most worthless class of persons - such as runaway  sailors, convicts who have escaped from ... NSW and VDL, keepers of grog-shops, and other vagabonds of dissolute habits, who ... practice frad, ... promote and take part in wars ... infect ... the natives with disease and a taste for ardent spirits. They really deserve the name which has been given them, `Devil's Missionaries'
